Date: 0/0/1941
Source: Numismatic History of NZ
Author: SUTHERLAND
Vol / Page: 228
Edition:
Quote: NEW ZEALAND CROSS, 1869. [heading] A silver maltese cross with a six pointed star in gold upon each limb. ... Institution, Order of the Governor in Council, dated 10 March, 1869. New Zealand Gazette 1869, p. 127. [229]  This cross was instituted by the Colonial Government and awarded to members of the local Militia, Volunteers, and Constabulary for acts of bravery and distinction.
